    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1896-01-30T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1896-01-30T00:00:00-05:00" n="347"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d347">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Eustis</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Olney</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1896-01-30">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 30, 1896</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Foreigner in mine of 28th is a mistake in ciphering. It should be Frenchman. Mr.
                    Clunet repeats that there is no difference between foreigner and Frenchman,
                    except with regard to securities for costs. Referring to your cable of the 22d,
                    the consul at Marseilles has been unable to find out positively under whose
                    charge Waller was during voyage. He believes, however, he was in charge of the
                    captain of the boat.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Eustis</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
